OL,3,CReverend left devastated after WW1
OL,4,Cplaques stolen from churchyard gates
OL,6,FITV News Meridian's Tom Savvides
OL,7,Fvisited Christ Church Luton, in
OL,8,FChatham.
OL,10,FA reverend from Chatham has been left
OL,11,Fdevastated after a pair of plaques,
OL,12,Fcommemorating those from Medway who
OL,13,Fdied in the World War One, were stolen
OL,14,Ffrom her churchyard's lychgate.
OL,16,FThe two memorials, that belong to
OL,17,FChrist Church Luton, in Chatham, were
OL,18,Ftaken by vandals, and were discovered
OL,19,Fto be missing by the head gardener the
OL,20,Ffollowing day.
