OL,3,CReverend left devastated after WW1
OL,4,Cplaques stolen from churchyard gates
OL,6,F"We feel devastated as a church and as
OL,7,Fa community because they've been there
OL,8,Ffor over a hundred years so we give
OL,9,Fhonour and respect to those who gave
OL,10,Fup everything for us to be free and to
OL,11,Flive in a world of peace.
OL,13,F"There are still people in the
OL,14,Fmilitary from this area who have
OL,15,Frelatives who were on those plaques
OL,16,Fand who will come on Remembrance
OL,17,FSunday when we lay wreaths and have
OL,18,Four two minute's silence."
